title=\"Ptolemy\">Ptolemy</a>. 1930. <i>Die Harmonielehre des Klaudios Ptolemaios</i>, edited by Ingemar D\u00fcring. G\u00f6teborgs h\u00f6gskolas \u00e5rsskrift 36, 1930:1. G\u00f6teborg: Elanders boktr. aktiebolag. Reprint, New York: Garland Publishing, 1980.</cite></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation wikicite\" id=\"CITEREFPtolemy2000\">Ptolemy. 2000. <i>Harmonics</i>, translated and commentary by Jon Solomon. <a href=\"/wiki/Mnemosyne_(journal)\" title=\"Mnemosyne (journal)\">Mnemosyne</a>, Bibliotheca Classica Batava, Supplementum, 0169-8958, 203. Leiden and Boston: Brill. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/90-04-11591-9\" title=\"Special:BookSources/90-04-11591-9\">90-04-11591-9</a>.</cite></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation wikicite\" id=\"CITEREFSolomon1984\">Solomon, Jon. 1984. \"Towards a History of Tonoi\". <i>The Journal of Musicology</i> 3, no. 3 (Summer): 242\u201351.</cite></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Further_reading\">Further reading</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Octave_species&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Further reading\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation wikicite\" id=\"CITEREFAnon.n.d.\">Anon. n.d. \"<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.britannica.com/eb/article-9056731/octave-species\">Octave Species</a>\". Encyclopedia Britannica (online edition, accessed 5 September 2014)</cite></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation wikicite\" id=\"CITEREFChalmers1993\">Chalmers, John H. Jr. 1993. <i>Divisions of the Tetrachord</i>. Hanover, NH: Frog Peak Music. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-945996-04-7\" title=\"Special:Book